<Window x:Class="FileSizeAnalyzerGUI.HelpWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        Title="Help" Height="550" Width="600"
        WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner" ShowInTaskbar="False">
    <ScrollViewer Margin="15">
        <StackPanel>
            <TextBlock Text="FileSizeAnalyzer Pro Help" FontSize="18" FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,0,0,10"/>

            <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,5">Scanning</TextBlock>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                1. Select a drive from the dropdown or click 'Browse' to choose a specific folder. You can also type a path directly into the text box.
                <LineBreak/>
                2. Click the 'Scan' button to begin the analysis. The scan can be stopped at any time with the 'Stop Scan' button.
            </TextBlock>

            <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,5">Filtering</TextBlock>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                - Use the dropdown menus to filter results by file size or date modified.
                <LineBreak/>
                - In the text box, you can filter by multiple file extensions. Separate them with a comma or semicolon (e.g., .jpg, .log; .tmp).
                <LineBreak/>
                - Click 'Apply Filters' to update the 'File List' tab with your filter criteria.
                <LineBreak/>
                - You can save a combination of filters by clicking 'Save Filter...' and giving it a name. Load it later from the 'Load Filter' dropdown.
            </TextBlock>

            <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,5">Interacting with Results</TextBlock>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                - Right-click on any file or folder in the lists to open its location or move it to the Recycle Bin.
                <LineBreak/>
                - In the 'Duplicates' tab, you can right-click a duplicate group header to auto-select all but the newest or oldest file for easy cleanup.
            </TextBlock>

            <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,5">Settings &amp; Exclusions</TextBlock>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                - Go to <Bold>File -&gt; Settings</Bold> to open the Exclusion List manager.
                <LineBreak/>
                - Add folder paths or file patterns to this list to ignore them during scans. Each pattern should be on a new line.
                <LineBreak/>
                - Use '*' as a wildcard. For example: <Bold>*.tmp</Bold> (excludes all temp files), <Bold>C:\Users\*\AppData</Bold> (excludes the AppData folder for all users).
            </TextBlock>

            <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,5">Command-Line Usage</TextBlock>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                The application can be run from a command prompt for automated scans.
                <LineBreak/>
                <Bold>Required:</Bold> -path "C:\Your\Folder"
                <LineBreak/>
                <Bold>Optional:</Bold>
                <LineBreak/>
                -export "report.csv" (Exports the results to a CSV file)
                <LineBreak/>
                -exit (Closes the app after scanning and exporting)
                <LineBreak/>
                -no-skip-system (Includes system files in the scan)
                <LineBreak/>
                -no-skip-windows (Includes the Windows directory in the scan)
            </TextBlock>

        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Window>
